1
00:00:46,507 --> 00:00:48,007
- Pil Sung! 
 - Go Pil Sung!

2
00:00:48,007 --> 00:00:49,897
Pil Sung! 
    

3
00:00:49,897 --> 00:00:51,087
Pil Sung!

4
00:00:51,087 --> 00:00:53,347
Pil Sung, are you okay?

5
00:00:53,347 --> 00:00:55,457
What happened?

6
00:00:55,457 --> 00:00:58,507
Mom, I'm okay, but the President...

7
00:00:59,677 --> 00:01:02,227
Oh, my! Soo Yeon!

8
00:01:02,227 --> 00:01:05,927
Soo Yeon! Soo Yeon, open your eyes!

9
00:01:05,927 --> 00:01:08,397
Ma Ri, what happened?

10
00:01:08,397 --> 00:01:11,227
A wall fell on her on the set

11
00:01:11,227 --> 00:01:15,007
and Mom tried to protect Pil Sung, and this is what happened.

12
00:01:15,007 --> 00:01:18,017
My mom won't wake up, no matter how much I try to wake her.

13
00:01:18,017 --> 00:01:21,437
What? She was trying to protect Pil Sung?

14
00:01:22,367 --> 00:01:25,447
No... No, not my Pil Sung!

15
00:01:25,447 --> 00:01:27,680
Pil Sung!

16
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:34,880


17
00:01:34,880 --> 00:01:36,637
Mom, Mom, what are you doing?

18
00:01:36,637 --> 00:01:38,297
Wake up, Mom.

19
00:01:38,297 --> 00:01:40,097
Open your eyes, Mom!

20
00:01:40,097 --> 00:01:42,647
Mom! Mom!

21
00:01:45,087 --> 00:01:48,587
Mom, can you see me?

22
00:01:48,587 --> 00:01:50,347
It's me!

23
00:01:50,347 --> 00:01:51,617
Soo Yeon, are you okay?

24
00:01:51,617 --> 00:01:53,777
Are you awake now?

25
00:01:54,377 --> 00:01:56,167
Where's Pil Sung?

26
00:01:56,167 --> 00:01:59,847
President, I'm here. I'm okay.

27
00:02:03,037 --> 00:02:05,397
Yes, Director Go.

28
00:02:05,397 --> 00:02:07,527
Are you sure you're okay?

29
00:02:08,107 --> 00:02:09,667
Yes.

30
00:02:12,657 --> 00:02:19,677
President Jang, you must've worried a lot about Pil Sung getting hurt.

31
00:02:21,007 --> 00:02:23,847
Doctor, are my mom and oppa okay?

32
00:02:23,847 --> 00:02:27,337
There's nothing wrong with Director Go, according to the test results.

33
00:02:27,337 --> 00:02:30,497
But Ms. Jang bruised her knee and shoulder.

34
00:02:30,497 --> 00:02:34,687
She'll have to take medicine and receive physical therapy for now.

35
00:02:35,317 --> 00:02:37,057
 Yes. 

36
00:02:37,057 --> 00:02:38,957
Thank you.

37
00:02:40,027 --> 00:02:44,457
I'm glad nothing worse happened.

38
00:02:44,457 --> 00:02:49,827
Pil Sung is totally fine. How did you get so injured, President Jang?

39
00:02:49,827 --> 00:02:55,187
My mom held Pil Sung like this to protect him, and they fell.

40
00:02:58,297 --> 00:03:04,307
Soo Yeon, thank you so much for saving Pil Sung. But...

41
00:03:04,307 --> 00:03:07,107
I'm so sorry you got injured.

42
00:03:07,107 --> 00:03:10,527
I feel so guilty about it. I'm sorry.

43
00:03:10,527 --> 00:03:12,527
It's okay, Seon Yeong.

44
00:03:12,527 --> 00:03:16,087
I'm totally fine. I'm really okay.

45
00:03:16,087 --> 00:03:20,337
The doctor said I was fine, too.

46
00:03:22,697 --> 00:03:25,377
Honey, what happened?

47
00:03:25,377 --> 00:03:26,757
How did you get into an accident?

48
00:03:26,757 --> 00:03:28,837
Are you okay?

49
00:03:29,867 --> 00:03:31,597
I'm okay.

50
00:03:31,597 --> 00:03:34,177
They said I'm totally fine.

51
00:03:40,057 --> 00:03:42,427
My gosh, my gosh.

52
00:03:42,427 --> 00:03:47,607
If it wasn't for your friend, something bad could've happened to Pil Sung.

53
00:03:47,607 --> 00:03:49,757
I know.

54
00:03:49,757 --> 00:03:56,587
How could she throw her fragile body to save Pil Sung?

55
00:03:57,317 --> 00:04:01,247
Your friend must really care for him a lot.

56
00:04:01,247 --> 00:04:03,507
She paid him so much contract money, too.

57
00:04:03,507 --> 00:04:05,847
And now she saved his life.

58
00:04:06,497 --> 00:04:12,747
Pil Sung, you'll have to be loyal to President Jang from now on.

59
00:04:12,747 --> 00:04:14,177
Of course.

60
00:04:14,177 --> 00:04:18,387
I didn't know she cared about me this much, either.

61
00:04:18,387 --> 00:04:22,197
You still need to relax. Rest upstairs.

62
00:04:22,197 --> 00:04:24,997
- Okay, I'll go upstairs. 
 - Yes, go upstairs.

63
00:04:24,997 --> 00:04:27,917
Hey, Myeong Dong. Get me some water.

64
00:04:27,917 --> 00:04:30,317
My heart is still racing so much.

65
00:04:30,317 --> 00:04:32,547
 - Okay.  
 - Aigoo.

66
00:04:35,047 --> 00:04:38,547
I'm glad Soo Yeon didn't get injured more.

67
00:04:38,547 --> 00:04:43,517
What if something terrible happened to her trying to save Pil Sung?

68
00:04:43,517 --> 00:04:47,557
I felt so bad that I couldn't face Chairman Gong earlier at the hospital.

69
00:04:47,557 --> 00:04:51,617
I know. I don't even want to think about it.

70
00:04:51,617 --> 00:04:54,287
By the way, CEO Jang...

71
00:04:54,287 --> 00:04:57,917
She said, "Pil Sung, my Pil Sung," unconsciously.

72
00:04:57,917 --> 00:05:00,337
Why was she calling for him in that situation?

73
00:05:00,337 --> 00:05:02,387
As if he was her child.

74
00:05:02,387 --> 00:05:06,777
One might've thought he was her son.

75
00:05:06,777 --> 00:05:10,307
It's because she got injured saving him, I'm sure.

76
00:05:11,127 --> 00:05:16,137
Soo Yeon has cared for Pil Sung since he was a baby.

77
00:05:17,357 --> 00:05:22,057
I'm too lucky to have a friend like her.

78
00:05:22,057 --> 00:05:24,587
You sure are lucky to have a good friend.

79
00:05:24,587 --> 00:05:28,027
You're lucky to have your husband, too? Right?

80
00:05:28,027 --> 00:05:32,247
Pardon? My husband? I'm lucky?

81
00:05:32,247 --> 00:05:34,997
W-What? She's right.

82
00:05:34,997 --> 00:05:41,240
Seriously, you always say nothing but truths.

83
00:05:42,077 --> 00:05:44,927
Yes, yes. You're right.

84
00:05:45,697 --> 00:05:47,947
Gosh, I got so scared.

85
00:05:49,767 --> 00:05:57,047
My gosh, how could you throw yourself to save that big man?

86
00:05:57,047 --> 00:05:59,467
We almost had a funeral today.

87
00:05:59,467 --> 00:06:00,877
I know.

88
00:06:00,877 --> 00:06:03,927
We can't break our bones at our age.

89
00:06:03,927 --> 00:06:06,747
How could you throw yourself to save Pil Sung?

90
00:06:06,747 --> 00:06:10,027
Were you that worried about Seon Yeong's son getting hurt?

91
00:06:11,787 --> 00:06:14,837
How could I just let someone get injured?

92
00:06:14,837 --> 00:06:17,687
He got into that dangerous situation working for my company.

93
00:06:17,687 --> 00:06:19,627
Let's go inside for now.

94
00:06:19,627 --> 00:06:23,617
Right. I left the medicine in the car.

95
00:06:23,617 --> 00:06:27,107
Ma Ri, bring her to the room. I'll get her medicine.

96
00:06:27,107 --> 00:06:28,807
Okay, Dad.

97
00:06:28,807 --> 00:06:30,547
Let's go, Mom.

98
00:06:30,547 --> 00:06:35,007
Heavens helped her today. Seriously.

99
00:06:35,977 --> 00:06:39,317
She's so devoted to Seon Yeong's family.

100
00:06:39,317 --> 00:06:41,987
She risked her life to save her son this time.

101
00:06:41,987 --> 00:06:45,317
Seriously, what a touching friendship.

102
00:06:51,057 --> 00:06:53,017
Having a barbecue reminds me of something.

103
00:06:53,017 --> 00:06:56,977
You once got us ribs once.

104
00:06:56,977 --> 00:06:58,767
When we used to live in that grandpa's house.

105
00:06:58,767 --> 00:07:01,717
- Do you remember, Do Jun? 
 - I do.

106
00:07:01,717 --> 00:07:06,237
I don't know where you got the money, but you told us to eat as much as we'd like.

107
00:07:06,237 --> 00:07:09,767
I think we ate about 15 servings, the four of us.

108
00:07:10,367 --> 00:07:13,067
Ji Yeong must not remember it.

109
00:07:14,187 --> 00:07:17,417
I'm not sure what you're talking about.

110
00:07:17,967 --> 00:07:22,057
Gosh, seriously. Stop talking about something she doesn't even remember.

111
00:07:22,057 --> 00:07:24,607
Let's just eat. Seriously.

112
00:07:24,607 --> 00:07:28,957
Here. Do Ra, say ah.

113
00:07:28,957 --> 00:07:32,127
Mom, we agreed not to call her that.

114
00:07:32,127 --> 00:07:34,877
Oh, right. It came out of nowhere.

115
00:07:34,877 --> 00:07:37,607
We have to call her Ji Yeong from now on, okay?

116
00:07:37,607 --> 00:07:41,057
It'd be a disaster if people found out she was Do Ra.

117
00:07:41,057 --> 00:07:44,317
Ji Yeong, say ah. Ah.

118
00:07:44,317 --> 00:07:46,557
Okay.

119
00:07:53,457 --> 00:07:55,657
It's tasty.

120
00:07:55,657 --> 00:07:59,297
Thank you so much for caring for me so much.

121
00:07:59,297 --> 00:08:03,387
Gosh, don't thank me. We're a family.

122
00:08:03,387 --> 00:08:07,057
Do Jun, you say ah, too. Ah.

123
00:08:08,687 --> 00:08:10,807
I'll eat it myself.

124
00:08:10,807 --> 00:08:14,177
Come on, Mom wants to feed you.

125
00:08:14,177 --> 00:08:19,077
Yes, just take it. Her arms are hurting.

126
00:08:21,427 --> 00:08:24,647
Yes, yes, yes.

127
00:08:28,427 --> 00:08:30,477
Mom, why are you crying?

128
00:08:32,917 --> 00:08:37,807
The four of us having a meal together...

129
00:08:37,807 --> 00:08:40,067
feels like a dream.

130
00:08:40,067 --> 00:08:42,337
I'm so happy.

131
00:08:42,337 --> 00:08:44,827
Gosh, Mom. Why are you doing this now?

132
00:08:45,847 --> 00:08:48,087
You're making me tear up.

133
00:08:49,977 --> 00:08:51,837
Let's not ever...

134
00:08:52,837 --> 00:08:54,797
be separated and live together like this.

135
00:08:54,797 --> 00:09:00,447
We can't afford Korean beef, but pork belly makes us so happy.

136
00:09:01,047 --> 00:09:05,157
Ji Yeong, you don't remember, but you're my daughter,

137
00:09:05,157 --> 00:09:10,147
Do Sik's younger sister, and Do Jun's older sister, okay?

138
00:09:11,007 --> 00:09:14,017
Okay, got it.

139
00:09:14,687 --> 00:09:16,707
I'm so happy, too.

140
00:09:16,707 --> 00:09:21,187
My Do Ra... I mean, Ji Yeong is alive and well like this.

141
00:09:23,347 --> 00:09:27,177
Seriously. Why are we doing this during a meal?

142
00:09:27,177 --> 00:09:29,027
Let's eat.

143
00:09:29,027 --> 00:09:35,427
Things are still awkward, but we'll get used to it once we start living together.

144
00:09:35,427 --> 00:09:37,307
Yes, Ahjumma.

145
00:09:37,307 --> 00:09:43,327
I'm happy to have a family like this, too.

146
00:09:44,077 --> 00:09:46,557
I wish she'd called me "Mom" when it's just us.

147
00:09:46,557 --> 00:09:49,607
She keeps calling me "Ahjumma."

148
00:09:49,607 --> 00:09:52,227
Mom, we agreed to take things slow.

149
00:09:52,227 --> 00:09:54,817
She'll get her memories back soon.

150
00:09:54,817 --> 00:09:58,947
Yes, yes. Let's take it slow. Take it slow.

151
00:09:58,947 --> 00:10:04,757
And Ji Yeong, you can call me "Ahjumma" forever. It's okay. It's okay.

152
00:10:04,757 --> 00:10:06,647
I'm sorry.

153
00:10:07,187 --> 00:10:10,957
Don't apologize. I said it's okay. It's okay.

154
00:10:10,957 --> 00:10:14,947
Let's eat. Let's eat. Come on and eat. Hurry, eat.

155
00:10:16,327 --> 00:10:18,157
Eat, eat.

156
00:10:18,157 --> 00:10:19,787
Let's eat.

157
00:10:36,937 --> 00:10:39,547
Grandma, what are you up to?

158
00:10:39,547 --> 00:10:43,277
What do you mean? I'm about to go to bed.

159
00:10:44,097 --> 00:10:46,867
What? Is something going on?

160
00:10:47,407 --> 00:10:49,867
Do I call only when something's going on?

161
00:10:49,867 --> 00:10:52,227
Everything's fine.

162
00:10:52,227 --> 00:10:54,287
How about you? You're okay, right?

163
00:10:54,287 --> 00:10:58,387
Did you go somewhere random singing the national anthem again?

164
00:10:58,387 --> 00:11:00,907
No, no.

165
00:11:00,907 --> 00:11:06,607
Deok Ja would've called you if I had gone berzerk.

166
00:11:06,607 --> 00:11:10,937
 Is it because I'm happy you're in a show? 

167
00:11:10,937 --> 00:11:13,627
 I'm totally fine these days. 

168
00:11:13,627 --> 00:11:18,907
Ji Yeong, the neighbors saw you on TV

169
00:11:18,907 --> 00:11:21,377
and they say you became successful.

170
00:11:21,377 --> 00:11:26,067
 My shoulders are almost touching the sky these days because of pride!. 

171
00:11:26,707 --> 00:11:27,927
Really?

172
00:11:27,927 --> 00:11:29,527
 Yes. 

173
00:11:29,527 --> 00:11:33,357
So, don't worry about me at all

174
00:11:33,357 --> 00:11:37,467
and just focus on your job, okay?

175
00:11:37,467 --> 00:11:39,897
Okay, Grandma.

176
00:11:39,897 --> 00:11:45,477
You know... I love you the most in the world, right?

177
00:11:45,477 --> 00:11:51,907
 I love you the most in the world, too. 

178
00:11:51,907 --> 00:11:54,337
Thank you, Grandma.

179
00:11:56,317 --> 00:11:58,497
Thank you, Grandma.

180
00:12:00,407 --> 00:12:02,417
I love you.

181
00:12:04,087 --> 00:12:06,417
I love you, Grandma.

182
00:12:29,527 --> 00:12:33,447
 Soo Yeon's company made me an amazing offer. 

183
00:12:33,447 --> 00:12:36,027
 Then, the CEO did that on her own? 

184
00:12:36,027 --> 00:12:37,497
 Without even asking you? 

185
00:12:37,497 --> 00:12:40,467
 No, not my Pil Sung! 

186
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:42,317
 Pil Sung! 

187
00:12:43,107 --> 00:12:44,877
How strange.

188
00:12:45,677 --> 00:12:47,687
How strange.

189
00:12:48,307 --> 00:12:51,657
This is more than just strange.

190
00:12:54,317 --> 00:12:57,167
Mom, why do you keep mumbling instead of sleeping?

191
00:12:57,167 --> 00:13:00,247
What do you find so strange, exactly?

192
00:13:00,917 --> 00:13:04,367
Myeong Dong, don't you find it strange?

193
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:06,127
Find what strange?

194
00:13:06,127 --> 00:13:10,267
She almost died because the wall fell on her.

195
00:13:10,267 --> 00:13:15,047
But she wasn't calling for her daughter, Ma Ri, or her husband.

196
00:13:15,047 --> 00:13:19,067
Why did she call for Pil Sung in that situation?

197
00:13:19,067 --> 00:13:21,427
So desperately, too.

198
00:13:21,427 --> 00:13:23,577
Mom, are you still talking about that?

199
00:13:23,577 --> 00:13:29,977
It's probably because she passed out saving Pil Sung.

200
00:13:29,977 --> 00:13:32,537
That's why I find it strange.

201
00:13:32,537 --> 00:13:37,037
Why would she call for Pil Sung in that situation?

202
00:13:38,277 --> 00:13:42,017
And you said this, too.

203
00:13:42,017 --> 00:13:46,847
Amazingly, she offered him that much contract money with Pil Sung's experience.

204
00:13:46,847 --> 00:13:51,507
Why? Why did she pay him twice as much to hire him?

205
00:13:52,477 --> 00:13:57,277
She's always been too generous to Pil Sung.

206
00:13:57,277 --> 00:14:01,657
She always sent tons of presents and food whenever he was celebrating something.

207
00:14:02,737 --> 00:14:10,570
But she risked her life to save him this time.

208
00:14:11,297 --> 00:14:12,897
Who would...

209
00:14:12,897 --> 00:14:15,767
Who would do that for a friend's son?

210
00:14:16,637 --> 00:14:20,967
So? What are you trying to say right now?

211
00:14:20,967 --> 00:14:22,737
Hey...

212
00:14:23,697 --> 00:14:26,987
No, no. It's just strange.

213
00:14:28,357 --> 00:14:31,377
Seriously, why wake me up for this?

214
00:14:39,887 --> 00:14:44,137
It's strange. It's strange.

215
00:14:44,137 --> 00:14:47,477
This isn't more than just strange.

216
00:14:50,657 --> 00:14:53,707
You didn't have to get us a meal, Pil Sung.

217
00:14:53,707 --> 00:14:56,327
I felt so bad and grateful toward you.

218
00:14:56,327 --> 00:14:58,377
You got injured saving me.

219
00:14:58,377 --> 00:15:00,357
Is it okay to come to work already?

220
00:15:00,357 --> 00:15:03,157
Of course. I came out because I'm okay.

221
00:15:03,157 --> 00:15:05,417
I feel okay since I took medicine and got good sleep.

222
00:15:05,417 --> 00:15:07,477
How about you? Are you really okay?

223
00:15:07,477 --> 00:15:10,817
Yes, I'm fine, thanks to you.

224
00:15:10,817 --> 00:15:12,547
Thank you so much.

225
00:15:12,547 --> 00:15:16,477
How many times did you thank me? Stop now.

226
00:15:17,187 --> 00:15:20,347
How long will you thank each other for?

227
00:15:20,347 --> 00:15:22,117
Enough with the pleasantries.

228
00:15:22,117 --> 00:15:25,217
How about we start eating now?

229
00:15:26,177 --> 00:15:27,647
Shall we?

230
00:15:27,647 --> 00:15:30,577
- Let's eat. 
 - Enjoy, President Jang.

231
00:15:30,577 --> 00:15:33,307
- The blue one. 
 - This blue one?

232
00:15:39,187 --> 00:15:41,047
Yes, yes, yes.

233
00:15:47,257 --> 00:15:49,897
No! What happened?

234
00:15:49,897 --> 00:15:51,867
Isn't it working?

235
00:15:52,807 --> 00:15:54,387
I got it!

236
00:15:55,537 --> 00:15:57,387
- Try again. 
 - Okay, okay.

237
00:15:57,387 --> 00:15:59,577
No, no. I can get it. I can get it.

238
00:16:08,847 --> 00:16:12,247
- Again! Get another one! 
 - Another one? Okay.

239
00:16:14,837 --> 00:16:21,287
 Yes, I hope Pil sung and Ma Ri continue to get along like this. 

240
00:16:21,287 --> 00:16:23,577
 I hope they continue to be happy like this. 

241
00:16:23,577 --> 00:16:25,057
- This one, right? 
 - Yes.

242
00:16:25,057 --> 00:16:27,147
Go further.

243
00:16:28,127 --> 00:16:29,877
Gosh, it's so hot.

244
00:16:29,877 --> 00:16:31,507
- Ji Yeong. 
 - Yes.

245
00:16:31,507 --> 00:16:37,597
I'll make your favorite, kimchijjim, with ribs.

246
00:16:37,597 --> 00:16:41,347
Whenever you finished a strict diet for a shoot,

247
00:16:41,347 --> 00:16:43,977
you always wanted my kimchijjim with ribs.

248
00:16:43,977 --> 00:16:46,577
You ate two bowls of rice easily.

249
00:16:46,577 --> 00:16:47,967
Was I like that?

250
00:16:47,967 --> 00:16:51,067
I still like kimchijjim with ribs.

251
00:16:51,067 --> 00:16:55,537
Oh, my. You lost your memory, but your taste buds haven't changed.

252
00:17:01,536 --> 00:17:05,376
Yes, this is Baek Mi Ja of Bbaek Entertainment.

253
00:17:05,376 --> 00:17:09,066
 A nightclub wants Ms. Kim to perform as the market lady 

254
00:17:09,066 --> 00:17:12,646
 from "Don't Lie to Me." Do you want her to do it? 

255
00:17:12,646 --> 00:17:16,476
 There will be 10 shows. I'll negotiate the pay. 

256
00:17:16,476 --> 00:17:18,576
Excuse me.

257
00:17:18,576 --> 00:17:21,746
