266
00:17:47,926 --> 00:17:49,796
Hand me those.

267
00:17:58,766 --> 00:18:03,286
You're preparing the restaurant opening well, right?

268
00:18:03,286 --> 00:18:07,956
Of course, I am. Everything is going perfectly.

269
00:18:07,956 --> 00:18:09,236
- You mean it, right? 
 - Of course. I'll really surprise you this time.

270
00:18:09,236 --> 00:18:14,396
- You mean it, right? 
 - Of course. I'll really surprise you this time.

271
00:18:15,266 --> 00:18:20,536
I'm opening a restaurant thanks to Pil Sung.

272
00:18:20,536 --> 00:18:23,236
We raised our son well, right?

273
00:18:23,236 --> 00:18:27,646
Yes, we're so lucky to have him.

274
00:18:28,896 --> 00:18:35,406
Yes, I'll work hard and pay Pil Sung back.

275
00:18:35,406 --> 00:18:40,886
And I'll buy him a nice apartment when he gets married, too.

276
00:18:40,886 --> 00:18:43,156
- Gosh, really? 
 - Of course.

277
00:18:43,156 --> 00:18:45,926
My gosh! How exciting!

278
00:18:49,426 --> 00:18:55,376
Jin Dan, why did you start drinking again?

279
00:18:55,376 --> 00:18:57,746
You said you'd get your act together.

280
00:18:57,746 --> 00:19:01,686
The in-laws' gathering is next week. You can't be like this.

281
00:19:03,116 --> 00:19:04,806
Mom,

282
00:19:06,256 --> 00:19:09,036
can we push back the in-laws' gathering?

283
00:19:09,036 --> 00:19:11,296
Why would you push it back?

284
00:19:12,326 --> 00:19:14,696
Why are we rushing it so much?

285
00:19:14,696 --> 00:19:17,056
It's not like we'd get married immediately.

286
00:19:18,306 --> 00:19:22,786
Gong Jin Dan, will you keep saying "Do Ra" again?

287
00:19:22,786 --> 00:19:24,886
Is this because of her?

288
00:19:24,886 --> 00:19:27,646
Are you still not back to your senses?

289
00:19:28,956 --> 00:19:30,726
Gosh, I don't know.

290
00:19:30,726 --> 00:19:33,926
I don't know why I'm like this, either.

291
00:19:33,926 --> 00:19:36,146
What do we do with you?

292
00:19:37,856 --> 00:19:40,106
My gosh. 
    

293
00:19:40,106 --> 00:19:45,076
Hyeon Cheol, this is our restaurant, right?

294
00:19:45,076 --> 00:19:47,866
Yes, Mom. This is our restaurant.

295
00:19:47,866 --> 00:19:49,726
Congratulations, Oppa.

296
00:19:49,726 --> 00:19:51,026
Thank you.

297
00:19:51,026 --> 00:19:52,926
Congratulations, Father.

298
00:19:52,926 --> 00:19:54,916
Thank you.

299
00:19:54,916 --> 00:20:00,056
I paid off the loan and got a nice restaurant like this, thanks to you.

300
00:20:00,056 --> 00:20:02,076
I'll work hard.

301
00:20:02,076 --> 00:20:05,216
We'll work hard and pay you back in full.

302
00:20:05,216 --> 00:20:07,326
What are you talking about? I gave you that money.

303
00:20:07,326 --> 00:20:09,316
Gosh, no.

304
00:20:09,316 --> 00:20:12,416
You have to work and pay back the contract money.

305
00:20:12,416 --> 00:20:16,236
How could I just take your hard-earned money?

306
00:20:16,236 --> 00:20:20,606
Parents and children need to be financially independent, too.

307
00:20:20,606 --> 00:20:23,466
Yes, I agree with Mom.

308
00:20:23,466 --> 00:20:26,406
Much, much later, then.

309
00:20:26,406 --> 00:20:29,506
It's big. There's endless space back there.

310
00:20:29,506 --> 00:20:32,196
This is so great.

311
00:20:32,196 --> 00:20:33,636
Welcome.

312
00:20:33,636 --> 00:20:36,286
Two people? Over there, please.

313
00:20:38,406 --> 00:20:42,396
Gosh, Soo Yeon! Ma Ri! What brings you here?

314
00:20:42,396 --> 00:20:46,886
What do you mean? We couldn't miss your opening.

315
00:20:46,886 --> 00:20:50,986
Jin Taek wanted to come, too, but he suddenly had to attend a seminar in Jeju-do.

316
00:20:50,986 --> 00:20:54,116
He said he's sorry and he'll make sure to come next time.

317
00:20:54,116 --> 00:20:58,256
He sent us the beautiful garland. That's enough.

318
00:20:58,256 --> 00:21:00,846
Seeing the garland from the APP Group's chairman,

319
00:21:00,846 --> 00:21:06,836
the other store owners asked us how we knew him.

320
00:21:06,836 --> 00:21:09,166
Hyeon Cheol is feeling so confident.

321
00:21:09,166 --> 00:21:11,276
He's been smiling all day.

322
00:21:11,276 --> 00:21:13,546
Should I tell him to send one every day, then?

323
00:21:13,546 --> 00:21:16,556
Gosh, come on.

324
00:21:16,556 --> 00:21:18,166
You came.

325
00:21:18,166 --> 00:21:19,876
- Yes, Pil Sung. 
 - Hi, Oppa.

326
00:21:19,876 --> 00:21:21,786
Hi, Ma Ri. You should eat.

327
00:21:21,786 --> 00:21:23,606
Come this way.

328
00:21:24,576 --> 00:21:26,396
Let's go.

329
00:21:28,776 --> 00:21:31,046
Give me that.

330
00:21:31,046 --> 00:21:33,046
Pil Sung, have a seat. I'll grill instead.

331
00:21:33,046 --> 00:21:36,036
No, we grill for you here.

332
00:21:36,036 --> 00:21:38,236
I'll make it tasty for you.

333
00:21:43,646 --> 00:21:45,536
Look how sweaty you got.

334
00:21:47,966 --> 00:21:49,686
Thank you.

335
00:21:52,946 --> 00:21:56,396
Why would she wipe the sweat off someone else's son's face?

336
00:21:57,996 --> 00:22:02,856
Why would he do that for a man in his 30s?

337
00:22:02,856 --> 00:22:04,296
I know, huh?

338
00:22:04,296 --> 00:22:06,726
That's a bit much.

339
00:22:06,726 --> 00:22:12,266
I know she's Seon Yeong's friend, but people might get the wrong idea.

340
00:22:12,266 --> 00:22:13,926
Wrong idea?

341
00:22:13,926 --> 00:22:15,646
Like what?

342
00:22:15,646 --> 00:22:17,346
Huh?

343
00:22:17,346 --> 00:22:18,766
- It's nothing. 
 - Have some, Mother.

344
00:22:18,766 --> 00:22:22,666
Hey, hey. Your friend, Soo Yeon...

345
00:22:22,666 --> 00:22:25,676
just because Pil Sung was sweating...

346
00:22:25,676 --> 00:22:28,726
she wiped it off of his face like this.

347
00:22:28,726 --> 00:22:32,356
Who does that to a friend's son?

348
00:22:32,976 --> 00:22:35,206
Tell her not to do that anymore.

349
00:22:35,206 --> 00:22:37,146
It looks kind of weird.

350
00:22:37,146 --> 00:22:38,596
Mother, come on.

351
00:22:38,596 --> 00:22:42,336
Why is that weird? It's okay to wipe off someone's sweat.

352
00:22:42,336 --> 00:22:43,376
- Go ahead and eat. 
 - Excuse me.

353
00:22:43,376 --> 00:22:45,186
Yes.

354
00:22:52,026 --> 00:22:56,346
Why would she look at someone else's son like that?

355
00:22:57,736 --> 00:23:00,866
She's so strange.

356
00:23:02,606 --> 00:23:05,786
- Take care. 
 - Come back with Chairman next time.

357
00:23:05,786 --> 00:23:07,596
- Did you enjoy the food, Ma Ri? 
 - Yes.

358
00:23:07,596 --> 00:23:09,346
- Come back again. 
 - Okay.

359
00:23:09,346 --> 00:23:10,776
Thank you for coming.

360
00:23:10,776 --> 00:23:14,056
- Take care. 
 - Get back safely.

361
00:23:18,466 --> 00:23:21,206
Myeong Dong, this looks like Ma Ri's earring.

362
00:23:21,206 --> 00:23:23,276
I'll give this to her now.

363
00:23:23,276 --> 00:23:24,806
Okay.

364
00:23:28,455 --> 00:23:33,295
Mom, can I hang out here for a little longer?

365
00:23:34,125 --> 00:23:36,265
What do you mean you want to hang out here?

366
00:23:36,265 --> 00:23:38,365
Didn't you see how busy everyone was?

367
00:23:38,365 --> 00:23:41,295
Well, I don't mean I'll just hang out.

368
00:23:41,295 --> 00:23:44,215
I want to help them with Oppa, too.

369
00:23:44,215 --> 00:23:45,435
Do it next time.

370
00:23:45,435 --> 00:23:51,285
Since today's the opening day, it's too crowded and chaotic. Get in the car.

371
00:23:51,285 --> 00:23:53,975
I hate saying goodbye to Oppa like this all the time.

372
00:23:53,975 --> 00:23:56,695
I want to live with him in our house.

373
00:23:56,695 --> 00:23:59,455
PIl Sung is my oppa and your son.

374
00:23:59,455 --> 00:24:02,065
How long do we have to be separated like this?

375
00:24:02,065 --> 00:24:06,215
Ma Ri, you promised not to say that.

376
00:24:06,215 --> 00:24:08,105
Get in the car.

377
00:24:08,105 --> 00:24:09,795
Come on.

378
00:24:13,335 --> 00:24:15,845
Good girl. Get in.

379
00:24:29,475 --> 00:24:31,345
My goodness.

380
00:24:32,185 --> 00:24:34,335
What did I just hear?

381
00:24:35,275 --> 00:24:37,605
What did she say just now?

382
00:24:43,595 --> 00:24:45,375
Have a seat.

383
00:24:48,635 --> 00:24:51,945
Mom, lie down.

384
00:24:52,885 --> 00:24:55,515
Why are you suddenly dizzy?

385
00:24:55,515 --> 00:24:57,625
Did you overdo it today?

386
00:24:57,625 --> 00:25:00,465
What if you have anemia?

387
00:25:00,465 --> 00:25:02,575
Let's go to the hospital and get a blood test.

388
00:25:02,575 --> 00:25:05,725
I don't have anemia.

389
00:25:05,725 --> 00:25:09,355
It's because I'm in shock. I'm in shock.

390
00:25:09,355 --> 00:25:12,425
Shock? About what?

391
00:25:12,425 --> 00:25:15,405
Myeong Dong, I...

392
00:25:16,445 --> 00:25:20,445
I think I know who Pil Sung's biological mother is.

393
00:25:20,445 --> 00:25:23,055
Pil Sung's biological mother?

394
00:25:24,085 --> 00:25:27,445
What are you talking about all of a sudden?

395
00:25:27,445 --> 00:25:32,495
Myeong Dong, this is a secret between us two.

396
00:25:32,495 --> 00:25:35,025
You have to keep it a secret until we die.

397
00:25:35,025 --> 00:25:38,765
Especially from Pil Sung and your sister-in-law.

398
00:25:38,765 --> 00:25:40,615
Come on, seriously!

399
00:25:40,615 --> 00:25:45,075
Today is Oppa's opening day. Why are you wasting time instead of helping?

400
00:25:45,075 --> 00:25:52,155
Myeong Dong, Ma Ri's mom... your sister-in-law's friend, President Jang.

401
00:25:53,285 --> 00:25:57,255
She's Pil Sung's biological mother.

402
00:25:57,255 --> 00:26:01,015
Pil Sung is that woman's son.

403
00:26:04,795 --> 00:26:07,435
What are you talking about?

404
00:26:07,435 --> 00:26:11,245
This is no good. Let's ask the doctor if you have dementia.

405
00:26:11,245 --> 00:26:14,305
Come on! I don't have dementia...

406
00:26:14,945 --> 00:26:18,045
When I followed them to give Ma Ri her earrings back,

407
00:26:18,045 --> 00:26:21,405
I overheard clearly with these two ears.

408
00:26:21,405 --> 00:26:24,685
Do you know what Ma Ri and President Jang said?

409
00:26:24,685 --> 00:26:27,555
"How long do we have to be separated?

410
00:26:27,555 --> 00:26:31,345
Pil Sung is your son and my oppa."

411
00:26:31,345 --> 00:26:33,075
That's what she said.

412
00:26:33,075 --> 00:26:36,245
Mom, you're acting strange.

413
00:26:36,245 --> 00:26:38,455
Let's get you tested for dementia.

414
00:26:38,455 --> 00:26:41,095
Come on. What's wrong with you?

415
00:26:41,095 --> 00:26:43,535
It's because you're talking nonsense.

416
00:26:43,535 --> 00:26:45,815
Don't say stuff like that to anyone.

417
00:26:45,815 --> 00:26:49,785
You'd get arrested for defamation if you say that without evidence.

418
00:26:49,785 --> 00:26:56,725
And Ma Ri has said weird things about him since she likes him. Don't you know that?

419
00:26:58,375 --> 00:27:00,155
Is that why?

420
00:27:01,055 --> 00:27:03,415
I'm going back to the store.

421
00:27:05,425 --> 00:27:08,465
We're so busy because it's Oppa's opening day, but you're talking nonsense.

422
00:27:08,465 --> 00:27:11,585
What's wrong with you?

423
00:27:14,975 --> 00:27:17,695
Did I really hear that wrong?

424
00:27:18,695 --> 00:27:23,015
I don't think so. My ears work just fine.

425
00:27:25,255 --> 00:27:27,031
Am I wrong?

426
00:27:27,845 --> 00:27:29,495
- Cheers! 
 - Cheers!

427
00:27:29,495 --> 00:27:32,465
- Thank you. 
 - Thank you.

428
00:27:36,315 --> 00:27:40,015
Do Sik, don't skip the team dinner from now on.

429
00:27:40,015 --> 00:27:42,105
Stop disappearing all the time.

430
00:27:42,105 --> 00:27:43,995
Okay, I won't.

431
00:27:43,995 --> 00:27:46,645
The soju ad model is Kim Na Bi now.

432
00:27:46,645 --> 00:27:49,745
You're right. Wasn't it Jo Sa Ra before?

433
00:27:49,745 --> 00:27:52,935
Jo Sa Ra got cancelled because of prostitution.

434
00:27:52,935 --> 00:27:56,205
Park Do Ra killed herself because of it, too.

435
00:27:57,525 --> 00:28:00,575
Park Do Ra was innocent of that.

436
00:28:00,575 --> 00:28:04,095
What do you mean? There were articles about it, too.

437
00:28:04,095 --> 00:28:06,405
It was to pay off her mom's gambling debt.

438
00:28:06,405 --> 00:28:08,555
The photos at the hotel were everywhere, too.

439
00:28:08,555 --> 00:28:09,845
It's not true, I said.

440
00:28:09,845 --> 00:28:11,685
Why do you talk about it as if it is?

441
00:28:11,685 --> 00:28:13,125
What do you mean it isn't?

442
00:28:13,125 --> 00:28:15,565
You can still look it up on the internet.

443
00:28:15,565 --> 00:28:17,175
It's all fake news.

444
00:28:17,175 --> 00:28:19,465
Enough is enough, please.

445
00:28:19,985 --> 00:28:23,085
Geez, why is this asshole pissing me off?

446
00:28:23,085 --> 00:28:25,625
That's enough. Why are you ruining the mood?

447
00:28:25,625 --> 00:28:27,745
You're drunk. You're all drunk.

448
00:28:27,745 --> 00:28:31,095
Hey, why would you call it fake news?

449
00:28:31,095 --> 00:28:36,015
Should I show you a photo of Park Do Ra with a man at the hotel?

450
00:28:36,015 --> 00:28:42,075
It says she died out of shame after sleeping with someone for money.

451
00:28:44,125 --> 00:28:46,005
It's not true, you bastard.

452
00:28:46,855 --> 00:28:51,145
Hey, what are you? Are you her cousin or something?

453
00:28:51,145 --> 00:28:52,565
Or are you her older brother?

454
00:28:52,565 --> 00:28:54,975
Yes, I'm Park Do Ra's older brother.

455
00:28:55,885 --> 00:28:58,935
Die, you bastard!

456
00:29:04,745 --> 00:29:06,615
Hey! Park Do Sik!

457
00:29:06,615 --> 00:29:08,965
What happened? Why did you hit someone?

458
00:29:08,965 --> 00:29:10,845
You've never done this before!

459
00:29:10,845 --> 00:29:13,725
Excuse me, are you Mr. Park's mother?

460
00:29:13,725 --> 00:29:16,065
Yes, I'm his mother.

461
00:29:16,065 --> 00:29:18,715
I'm his younger sister.

462
00:29:18,715 --> 00:29:22,435
The victim is at the hospital. Just try to settle.

463
00:29:22,435 --> 00:29:25,405
It'd be a headache if it gets escalated.

464
00:29:25,405 --> 00:29:28,725
Looks like they blew off steam over drinks.

465
00:29:28,725 --> 00:29:30,925
No need to have a criminal record at a young age.

466
00:29:30,925 --> 00:29:32,975
He doesn't even have previous criminal records.

467
00:29:32,975 --> 00:29:35,025
You little. Seriously...

468
00:29:35,025 --> 00:29:37,465
Gosh. My goodness.

469
00:29:37,465 --> 00:29:39,365
Seriously.

470
00:29:42,205 --> 00:29:46,555
W-What did you say? 50 million won  (~$36K) ?

471
00:29:47,225 --> 00:29:50,615
We have no 50 million. We can't get that money.

472
00:29:50,615 --> 00:29:52,705
Please forgive us just once, sir.

473
00:29:52,705 --> 00:29:56,735
Send him to jail if you don't, then.

474
00:29:56,735 --> 00:29:59,165
Is Park Do Ra his sister or something?

475
00:29:59,165 --> 00:30:03,425
He did this to me by saying Park Do Ra died because she had sex for money.

476
00:30:03,425 --> 00:30:08,415
I can't settle unless you pay me 50 million, okay?

477
00:30:08,415 --> 00:30:10,965
Let the law take care of it! Let's!

478
00:30:10,965 --> 00:30:13,095
He should do time for doing this to me.

479
00:30:13,095 --> 00:30:16,505
My gosh, please have some of this.

480
00:30:16,505 --> 00:30:17,925
This, too. This, too.

481
00:30:17,925 --> 00:30:19,685
Please forgive him just once, Sir.

482
00:30:19,685 --> 00:30:21,595
We're sorry.

483
00:30:25,085 --> 00:30:28,855
I didn't know he got into a fight because of me.

484
00:30:28,855 --> 00:30:33,395
I don't even have five million. How will I get 50 million?

485
00:30:33,395 --> 00:30:35,925
Hold on. Should I call Do Jun?

486
00:30:38,115 --> 00:30:42,115
No, he must be living off his small wage.

487
00:30:42,115 --> 00:30:43,835
He can't have any money.

488
00:30:43,835 --> 00:30:46,865
Calling him would only make him worry.

489
00:30:47,865 --> 00:30:51,765
Have some water and calm down, Ahjumma.

490
00:30:54,915 --> 00:30:58,065
Hey, Ji Yeong. Do you have money, by chance?

491
00:30:58,065 --> 00:30:59,635
Could I use it if you do?

492
00:30:59,635 --> 00:31:02,535
We need to stop your brother from going to jail.

493
00:31:02,535 --> 00:31:07,075
I got five million back for the security deposit when I moved out of Director's house.

494
00:31:07,075 --> 00:31:08,645
Is that all you have?

495
00:31:08,645 --> 00:31:10,165
Yes.

496
00:31:12,115 --> 00:31:15,075
Hey, how about the contract fee you're getting from the drama?

497
00:31:15,075 --> 00:31:18,825
Ask Jae Dong when that'll get deposited. Hurry, hurry.

498
00:31:18,825 --> 00:31:20,425
Okay.

499
00:31:36,085 --> 00:31:37,675
President Lee, it's me.

500
00:31:37,675 --> 00:31:42,365
When will I receive the contract fee?

501
00:31:43,465 --> 00:31:47,675
Is that so? Okay.

502
00:31:48,525 --> 00:31:51,205
No, no. E-E-Everything's fine.

503
00:31:51,205 --> 00:31:52,665
I was just curious.

504
00:31:52,665 --> 00:31:55,135
Okay, okay. Bye.

505
00:31:56,415 --> 00:31:58,415
That won't work, either.

506
00:31:58,415 --> 00:32:02,585
I get 30% after the first shoot, but that needs to be used as project expenses.

507
00:32:02,585 --> 00:32:07,035
Gosh, what are we supposed to do, then?

508
00:32:09,115 --> 00:32:15,175
Oh, how about your grandma in the countryside? Does she have money?

509
00:32:15,175 --> 00:32:17,705
My grandma? Gosh.

510
00:32:17,705 --> 00:32:20,715
How would she have any money?

511
00:32:20,715 --> 00:32:22,895
What are we going to do about Do Sik?

512
